# NASA APOD API

This project is an API to obtain the astronomical picture of the day (APOD) from NASA, documented using Swagger.

## Structure
nasa-apod-api/
├── index.js # Application entry point.
├─── swaggerConfig.js # # Swagger configuration for documentation.
├─── package.json
├─── package-lock.json
└─── .env # File for environment variables (e.g. NASA_API_KEY).


## Installation.

1. **Clone the repository:**
   ````bash
   git clone https://tu-repositorio.git
   cd nasa-apod-api

Make sure you have a valid NASA API key to access the APOD API. You can obtain a key by registering at the NASA API Portal.

Create an .env file in the root directory of the project and add your API key:

NASA_API_KEY=YOUR_AP_KEY

## Execution

Once built, we will be able to access our microservice via

http://localhost:3000


## API documentation:

The API documentation is available at Swagger UI. Access http://localhost:3000/api-docs in your web browser to explore and test the API paths.

